news.title: Repco Home Finance posts net profit of Rs 80.76 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Repco Home Finance's consolidated total income stood at Rs 330.85 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 1.66 per cent from Rs 325.45 crore in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: K Raheja Corp buys rights for 1.53 lakh sq ft FSI in Mumbai for Rs 275 crore
news.para: The FSI rights are for the development of the free-sale component of a slum rehabilitation project in Wadala’s Shanti Nagar. The slum rehabilitation part of the project including the new tenements has been completed and has already received its Occupation Certificate (OC).

news.title: Brigade Enterprises sells properties worth Rs 2,618.5 crore in Apr-Dec 2022
news.para: In its investor presentation, the company highlighted that it has "achieved sales value of Rs 26,185 million (Rs 2,618.5 crore) during 9 months of FY23, a growth of 31 per cent over 9 month of FY22".

news.title: Shalimar Paints posts net loss of Rs 6.24 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Shalimar Paints' consolidated total income stood at Rs 130.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 31.36 per cent from Rs 99.01 crore in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Urbanrise buys 96.5 acre land from Reliance Capital in Chennai
news.para: Urbanrise said in a statement that it will develop a mega township project on the land parcel that has a "development potential of 13 million square feet with an expected revenue of Rs 7,000 crore."

news.title: Jaipur development body starts loan process for extension of metro
news.para: The state government granted financial approval for Metro Line 1D and Line 1C in October and November 2022 respectively. Under the Line 1D, metro services will be extended from Mansarovar to Ajmer Road (200 feet Bypass).

news.title: Residents in Haryana allege vested interest in Huda design
news.para: ​​The members have decided to meet the Haryana governor and submit one lakh signatures against the new “illegally amended building code of Huda (Haryana Urban Development Authority).”

news.title: Special camps in Trichy to resolve property tax issues
news.para: ​​The camps will be held across all five zonal corporation offices, including near TVS tollgate, Srirangam Gandhi Road, Allithurai Road and Palakkarai.

news.title: Mohali development body fined for delaying plot possession for over three years
news.para: Rahat Khanna, a resident of Sector 49, said the Gmada had opened a scheme offering 750 residential plots in IT City, Mohali.

news.title: Property owners hold protest in Chandigarh sector 17
news.para: The protesters said if the administration does not revise the SOPs, property owners will be forced to take to the streets.

news.title: Greater Noida: Connection still temporary, no electricity for a week in JKG Palm Court's common area
news.para: Claiming the builder has not taken a permanent electricity connection from the power department and runs JKG Palm Court on a temporary one, they protested against the builder on Sunday afternoon.

news.title: 'Middlemen siphoning off housing scheme funds' in Bengaluru
news.para: The beneficiaries should have a site of their own to apply for this programme. The area of the site should not exceed 600sqft. This year alone, about 5,000 people have applied for the scheme, according to the Palike.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's affiliate buys penthouse in Mumbai for Rs 230 crore
news.para: The developer has acquired the luxury pad spread over around 30,000 sq ft on the 63rd habitable floor of the project’s tower B through its affiliated company RS Developers, showed the registration documents accessed by ET.

news.title: Maxop Engineering's director buys bungalow in Delhi's Golf Links for Rs 68.5 crore
news.para: Arora purchased the property from Delhi-based Vaishnawi Energy Distribution Pvt Ltd, which had acquired it from Raj Singh Gehlot, the promoter of the Ambience group, for ₹80 crore.

news.title: China's Vanke to raise 15 billion yuan in private placement for projects
news.para: Vanke plans to sell up to 1.1 billion A-shares, representing 9.46% of its total share capital before the issuance, to up to 35 investors, the company said in a filing to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange on Sunday.
